author: @siddharthkotwal8823
text: Hey man, I really like this series. Your delivery is pretty awesome and relatable; somewhat similar to how I speak to myself in my head while working on a project :)   I had one general question as someone trying to learn CS. What is your approach to learning new mathematical/statistical material like ML? Say I pick up a book or a course, what are the best practices for striking the right balance between theory and practice? I often find it hard to get the applied skills (cos understanding the theory and algos properly saps my energy and then I move to the next algorithm!). Second, how often do you have to come back to these principles or examples? Would be great to have your advice!
